frequencies.name: NUMMELA TRAFIC
frequencies.remarks:
The runway lights can be operated as follows (using the aviation radio frequency 122.825):
Four clicks, with a one-second press and one-second interval, activate only the APAPI lights at brightness level two, suitable for daytime APAPI practice.
Five clicks, with a one-second press and one-second interval, activate both the runway and APAPI lights at brightness level one.
Six clicks, with a one-second press and one-second interval, activate both the runway and APAPI lights at brightness level two.
Seven clicks, with a one-second press and one-second interval, activate both the runway and APAPI lights at brightness level three.
